Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.91,0:00:20.41,Sayaka,,0,0,0,,You deceived us, didn't you?{騙してたのね。私達を}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.79,0:00:24.92,QB,,0,0,0,,I believe I precisely requested that you become a magical girl, didn't I?{僕は魔法少女になってくれって、きちんとお願いしたはずだよ？}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.38,0:00:29.30,QB,,0,0,0,,I omitted an explanation about what kind of thing the "reality of their figure" is, though.{実際の姿がどういうものか、説明を省略したけれど}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.93,0:00:35.93,Sayaka,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you inform me of that!?{何で教えてくれなかったのよ！}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.93,0:00:37.93,QB,,0,0,0,,Because you didn't ask.{訊かれなかったからさ}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.93,0:00:41.93,QB,,0,0,0,,If you didn't find out, it wouldn't have brought you any inconvenience to just go on without ever knowing, either.{知らなければ知らないままで、何の不都合もないからね}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.93,0:00:45.48,QB,,0,0,0,,In fact, that Mami girl never realized even at the very end.{事実、あのマミでさえ最後まで気づかなかった}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:52.40,QB,,0,0,0,,First off, you humans aren't aware of something like your soul's existence to begin with, are you?{そもそも君たち人間は、魂の存在なんて、最初から自覚できてないんだろう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.15,0:00:56.28,QB,,0,0,0,,Over there is nothing but a collection of neurons,{そこは神経細胞の集まりでしかないし}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.28,0:00:59.74,QB,,0,0,0,,and over there is just the center of a circulatory system.{そこは、循環器系の中枢があるだけだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.66,0:01:06.42,QB,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, when that can't maintain life, even a human's mind and soul will be annihilated.{そのくせ、生命が維持できなくなると、人間は精神まで消滅してしまう}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.42,0:01:13.17,QB,,0,0,0,,To prevent that from happening, I gave you girls your souls in a materialized form. One that you can hold and precisely protect.{そうならないよう、僕は君たちの魂を実体化し、手に取ってきちんと守れる形にしてあげた}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.72,0:01:16.80,QB,,0,0,0,,I'm hoping to make it a little bit safer for you to fight witches, you know.{少しでも安全に、魔女と戦えるようにね}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.80,0:01:20.10,Sayaka,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the big help! Such an unnecessary thing!{大きなお世話よ！そんな余計な事！}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.18,0:01:24.35,QB,,0,0,0,,You're thinking about those things called "battles" far too lightly.{君は戦いという物を甘く考え過ぎだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.48,0:01:31.73,QB,,0,0,0,,For example, how much do you think it would stimulate your body's sense of pain if a spear was stuck into your stomach?{例えば、お腹に槍が刺さった場合、肉体の痛覚がどれだけの刺激を受けるかって言うとね}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:45.71,QB,,0,0,0,,This is the original amount of pain you would receive.{これが本来の痛みだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.12,0:01:48.71,QB,,0,0,0,,It's just a single strike, but you can't move, right?{ただの一発でも、動けやしないだろう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.67,0:01:59.55,QB,,0,0,0,,At the end of your battle with Kyouko, you were able to stand up because this saved you from anything too intensely painful.{君が杏子との戦いで最後まで立っていられたのは、強過ぎる苦痛がセーブされていたからさ}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.97,0:02:03.77,QB,,0,0,0,,It was only possible because your consciousness isn't directly linked with your body.{君の意識が肉体と直結していないからこそ可能なことだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:07.52,QB,,0,0,0,,Due to this, your life extended past that battle.{おかげで君は、あの戦闘を生き延びることができた}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:18.53,QB,,0,0,0,,If you grew accustomed to it, you could also completely cut off all pain.{慣れてくれば、完全に痛みを遮断することもできるよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.03,0:02:23.53,QB,,0,0,0,,Although, if you did that, your movements would become dull, so I don't really recommend it.{もっとも、それはそれで動きが鈍るから、あまりオススメはしないけど}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:25.70,Sayaka,,0,0,0,,What for...?{何でよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.70,0:02:28.08,Sayaka,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to go through such an experience...?{どうして私達をこんな目に…！}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:32.54,QB,,0,0,0,,You had a desire that you wanted fulfilled, even if it meant accepting a fate of battle, right?{戦いの運命を受け入れてまで、君には叶えたい望みがあったんだろう？}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.13,0:02:35.55,QB,,0,0,0,,And that unmistakably became reality, didn't it?{それは間違いなく実現したじゃないか}
